HEADWORD: Misfeasance
<hw>Mis*fea"sance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. pref.
<ets>mes-</ets> wrong (L. <ets>minus</ets> less) + <ets>faisance</ets>
doing, fr. <ets>faire</ets> to do, L. <ets>facere</ets>. Cf.
<er>Malfeasance</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A trespass; a wrong
arising from an overt act; the improper doing of an act which a person
might lawfully do.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au>
<au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

